				\begin{document}$$ {m}_{c,g,a,w,y}=\frac{D_{c,g,a,w,y}}{\left({E}_{c,g,a,y}/52\right)} $$\end{document}mc,g,a,w,y=Dc,g,a,w,yEc,g,a,y/52

We follow Vanella (2017), which was presented in 2.2. To stabilize the variances in mortality rates, especially for older ages, we employ a logit transformation of the WASCSMRs (Vanella, 2017). We first perform PCA on the logit-WASCSMR time series such that we obtain a set of PCs with the ith PC being a linear combination of all logit-WASCSMRs:
