We then use a Monte Carlo simulation for each PC to simulate 10,000 trajectories of the weekly development of all PCs for 2020. Since the PCs are uncorrelated (Vanella, 2018), independent simulations of their future paths do not lead to biased estimations of mortality rates, which are then derived from these. The results consist of 10,000 trajectories of each PC, which can be retransformed into weekly trajectories of the logit-WASCSMR. For instance, let Πt be the simulation matrix of all PCs (10,000×152) in period t. The corresponding simulation matrix of the logit-WASCSMRs is then
